{"type":"message","id":"3e00a57b","parentId":"41806f61","timestamp":"2026-03-21T10:29:08.840Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Implementing board interaction**\n\nI need to implement board interaction and might start by inspecting if I can rewrite any WXML. It seems I don't need any special skills for this, so I'll proceed.\n\nShould I use existing memory? The user hasn't mentioned prior work, so probably not. I could write a state model in a separate helper module, and I can implement this using JS in the miniprogram.\n\nI'll focus on providing a board rendering grid with a coordinate map, relying on data arrays despite the lack of a full wx runtime. I wonder if I should integrate a rules engine. It looks like I can use `require` in WeChat, but I'm unsure about the module format. Should I stick to CommonJS or use ES modules?\n\n**Considering miniprogram setup**\n\nIf I’m working within the miniprogram environment, it looks like I can use `require` without a bundler. However, the source project might not be runnable as it is. Since the internal project can use TypeScript later, I should keep the current implementation coherent.\n\nI might switch to CommonJS for the miniprogram side, but there's an issue with imported module paths from `src` not being available. A simple solution could be to add a shared utility file that copies or re-exports logic. Even though it's redundant, creating a prototype bridge using direct logic from `src` might work, so I’ll focus on using local JS with `require`.\n\n**Adapting to miniprogram structure**\n\nIn the miniprogram runtime, the file system structure is different, and `../../src` won't exist after packaging. Instead, local modules should be placed in `miniprogram/utils` or within pages. I could create a `miniprogram/utils/chess-engine.js` to implement minimal board state mapping by adapting logic from the source modules.\n\nHowever, that might be too complicated. It might be simpler to have the game page manage the board state using a pure data model and leverage local helper functions to calculate legal moves, considering we already have a rules engine in the source.\n\n**Deciding on modules in miniprograms**\n\nI'm considering the environment for miniprograms. It seems like it mostly supports `module.exports` rather than ES modules. Existing pages are using `import`, which makes it tricky. If I don’t transpile, ES modules in the miniprogram `.js` files won’t follow the standard. Although WeChat miniprogram JS supports CommonJS too, so I should probably stick to CommonJS to keep it safe. I think it's best to standardize our miniprogram utilities and pages to CommonJS, while src can remain as ES modules.\n\n**Structuring the chess engine module**\n\nI’m planning to write the miniprogram utilities for the chess engine as a CommonJS export module, possibly based on the source files. The game.js page will utilize `require` to import `createGameState`, while the engine will require `chess-engine` from the same utilities folder. I might need to adjust `game-state.js` as well. Even though there’s a concern about copying large rules.js, it looks like the safest option will be to copy it into the miniprogram rather than risk any runtime issues.\n\n**Managing game page state**\n\nI'm focusing on game page state management, which involves initializing the board, handling selected pieces, managing legal moves, and noting any pending AI thinking. I’ll render the board as a 10x9 grid using a template with nested loops. The board can be represented as an array of rows, with each having cell objects. I need to compute piece labels using Chinese characters and set up a click handler to respond to cell taps. Lastly, I’ll update the game interface accordingly.\n\n**Connecting move logic to engine**\n\nI need to connect the move logic to the game engine, which involves functions like `createInitialBoard`, `getLegalMoves`, `advanceGame`, and `searchBestMove`. Handling piece selection is essential—if the user taps their piece, I should show the legal move targets. If they tap a legal target, I apply the move and, potentially for AI games, schedule the AI move afterward. I’ll also look into adding a restart button and maybe an undo feature, though it's not strictly necessary. Additionally, I want to display a status message and ensure proper board orientation and styling.\n\n**Implementing chess engine**\n\nI’m thinking about using flex wrap for the layout. I could check the README or package, but it doesn't seem necessary right now. I’m also considering updating tests, though I might skip that for now. I’ll write new files and think about adding a simple AI option. We could develop a gameState utility that includes the board, selected pieces, legal moves, and game mode to create a more complete state. I'll implement `miniprogram/utils/chess-engine.js` by adapting the source code for CommonJS, focusing on essential functions like creating the initial board, getting pieces, and advancing the game.\n\n**Considering file structure**\n\nI'm thinking about how to access the `src` directory when dealing with miniprogram files after the build. It seems like local development might allow relative paths, but it's not ideal. To avoid duplication, I could create a bridge file in `miniprogram/utils`, referencing `require('../../src/game/board.js')`. Although the `src` folder won’t be included in the miniprogram package, it could act as a source of truth. I could also consider adding an adapter in `miniprogram/utils/chess-engine.js` to streamline the process.\n\n**Creating chess engine module**\n\nI'm planning to create `miniprogram/utils/chess-engine.js` by mostly copying existing modules from `src` but adjusting for CommonJS exports. It should be around 400 lines, which sounds manageable. I don't need to copy every function, just the essential ones for the UI like `createInitialBoard`, `getLegalMoves`, and others. I might skip test helpers, using require/export for clarity. Next, I'll focus on rewriting `game.js`, updating the UI to show a board with 9 columns and 10 rows. I'll also need to add styles and helper functions for rendering pieces.\n\n**Building the board view**\n\nI want to use the pieces 将, 车, 马, 象, 士, 炮, 卒 for my chess game. My function `buildBoardView(board, selectedPieceId, legalMoves, lastMove)` will return rows of the board. For each cell, I might use a `cellKey` that combines x and y coordinates. I'll mark cells as `isSelected`, `isLegalTarget`, or `isLastMove`, and if there's a piece present, it will display its `text` and `className`. I'll also set up `legalTargets` as a string of coordinates and include `statusText` for better context.\n\n**Implementing board history**\n\nI'm considering how to track board history. We have the moveHistory in the board but lack snapshots of the previous states. I think we could reconstruct the board from the initial state using replayMoves, but that feels unnecessary. Instead, I could implement an undo feature by storing a `historySnapshots` array of previous boards. Each time a move is made, the current board gets pushed into this array. So, the `undo` function can just pop the last board and re-render it. I'll also consider adding a `getGameSummary` function to provide updates on the winner or game status.\n\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_3tqJJq7llc4Td6idYtJY1zoF","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"set -e\nBASE=/home/gem/workspace/agent/workspace/chinese-chess-minigame\ncat > \"$BASE/miniprogram/utils/chess-engine.js\" <<'EOF'\nconst BOARD_WIDTH = 9;\nconst BOARD_HEIGHT = 10;\n\nconst Side = Object.freeze({ RED: 'red', BLACK: 'black' });\nconst PieceType = Object.freeze({\n  ROOK: 'rook',\n  HORSE: 'horse',\n  ELEPHANT: 'elephant',\n  ADVISOR: 'advisor',\n  GENERAL: 'general',\n  CANNON: 'cannon',\n  SOLDIER: 'soldier',\n});\n\nfunction oppositeSide(side) {\n  return side === Side.RED ? Side.BLACK : Side.RED;\n}\n\nfunction isInsideBoard(x, y) {\n  return x >= 0 && x < BOARD_WIDTH && y >= 0 && y < BOARD_HEIGHT;\n}\n\nfunction createPiece(id, type, side, x, y) {\n  return { id, type, side, pos: { x, y }, alive: true };\n}\n\nfunction createInitialBoard() {\n  return {\n    pieces: [\n      createPiece('b-r1', PieceType.ROOK, Side.BLACK, 0, 0),\n      createPiece('b-h1', PieceType.HORSE, Side.BLACK, 1, 0),\n      createPiece('b-e1', PieceType.ELEPHANT, Side.BLACK, 2, 0),\n      createPiece('b-a1', PieceType.ADVISOR, Side.BLACK, 3, 0),\n      createPiece('b-g', PieceType.GENERAL, Side.BLACK, 4, 0),\n      createPiece('b-a2', PieceType.ADVISOR, Side.BLACK, 5, 0),\n      createPiece('b-e2', PieceType.ELEPHANT, Side.BLACK, 6, 0),\n      createPiece('b-h2', PieceType.HORSE, Side.BLACK, 7, 0),\n      createPiece('b-r2', PieceType.ROOK, Side.BLACK, 8, 0),\n      createPiece('b-c1', PieceType.CANNON, Side.BLACK, 1, 2),\n      createPiece('b-c2', PieceType.CANNON, Side.BLACK, 7, 2),\n      createPiece('b-s1', PieceType.SOLDIER, Side.BLACK, 0, 3),\n      createPiece('b-s2', PieceType.SOLDIER, Side.BLACK, 2, 3),\n      createPiece('b-s3', PieceType.SOLDIER, Side.BLACK, 4, 3),\n      createPiece('b-s4', PieceType.SOLDIER, Side.BLACK, 6, 3),\n      createPiece('b-s5', PieceType.SOLDIER, Side.BLACK, 8, 3),\n      createPiece('r-r1', PieceType.ROOK, Side.RED, 0, 9),\n      createPiece('r-h1', PieceType.HORSE, Side.RED, 1, 9),\n      createPiece('r-e1', PieceType.ELEPHANT, Side.RED, 2, 9),\n      createPiece('r-a1', PieceType.ADVISOR, Side.RED, 3, 9),\n      createPiece('r-g', PieceType.GENERAL, Side.RED, 4, 9),\n      createPiece('r-a2', PieceType.ADVISOR, Side.RED, 5, 9),\n      createPiece('r-e2', PieceType.ELEPHANT, Side.RED, 6, 9),\n      createPiece('r-h2', PieceType.HORSE, Side.RED, 7, 9),\n      createPiece('r-r2', PieceType.ROOK, Side.RED, 8, 9),\n      createPiece('r-c1', PieceType.CANNON, Side.RED, 1, 7),\n      createPiece('r-c2', PieceType.CANNON, Side.RED, 7, 7),\n      createPiece('r-s1', PieceType.SOLDIER, Side.RED, 0, 6),\n      createPiece('r-s2', PieceType.SOLDIER, Side.RED, 2, 6),\n      createPiece('r-s3', PieceType.SOLDIER, Side.RED, 4, 6),\n      createPiece('r-s4', PieceType.SOLDIER, Side.RED, 6, 6),\n      createPiece('r-s5', PieceType.SOLDIER, Side.RED, 8, 6),\n    ],\n    currentSide: Side.RED,\n    selectedPieceId: null,\n    lastMove: null,\n    moveHistory: [],\n    status: 'playing',\n    winner: null,\n  };\n}\n\nfunction cloneBoard(board) {\n  return {\n    ...board,\n    pieces: board.pieces.map((piece) => ({ ...piece, pos: { ...piece.pos } })),\n    lastMove: board.lastMove ? { ...board.lastMove, from: { ...board.lastMove.from }, to: { ...board.lastMove.to } } : null,\n    moveHistory: board.moveHistory.map((move) => ({ ...move, from: { ...move.from }, to: { ...move.to } })),\n  };\n}\n\nfunction getPieceAt(board, x, y) {\n  return board.pieces.find((piece) => piece.alive && piece.pos.x === x && piece.pos.y === y) || null;\n}\n\nfunction getPiecesBySide(board, side) {\n  return board.pieces.filter((piece) => piece.alive && piece.side === side);\n}\n\nfunction getGeneral(board, side) {\n  return board.pieces.find((piece) => piece.alive && piece.side === side && piece.type === PieceType.GENERAL) || null;\n}\n\nfunction inPalace(side, x, y) {\n  const palace = side === Side.RED ? { xMin: 3, xMax: 5, yMin: 7, yMax: 9 } : { xMin: 3, xMax: 5, yMin: 0, yMax: 2 };\n  return x >= palace.xMin && x <= palace.xMax && y >= palace.yMin && y <= palace.yMax;\n}\n\nfunction crossedRiver(side, y) {\n  return side === Side.RED ? y <= 4 : y >= 5;\n}\n\nfunction forwardDelta(side) {\n  return side === Side.RED ? -1 : 1;\n}\n\nfunction clearLine(board, from, to) {\n  const dx = Math.sign(to.x - from.x);\n  const dy = Math.sign(to.y - from.y);\n  let x = from.x + dx;\n  let y = from.y + dy;\n  while (x !== to.x || y !== to.y) {\n    if (getPieceAt(board, x, y)) return false;\n    x += dx;\n    y += dy;\n  }\n  return true;\n}\n\nfunction countBetween(board, from, to) {\n  const dx = Math.sign(to.x - from.x);\n  const dy = Math.sign(to.y - from.y);\n  let x = from.x + dx;\n  let y = from.y + dy;\n  let count = 0;\n  while (x !== to.x || y !== to.y) {\n    if (getPieceAt(board, x, y)) count += 1;\n    x += dx;\n    y += dy;\n  }\n  return count;\n}\n\nfunction addMove(board, piece, x, y, moves) {\n  if (!isInsideBoard(x, y)) return;\n  const target = getPieceAt(board, x, y);\n  if (target && target.side === piece.side) return;\n  moves.push({\n    pieceId: piece.id,\n    from: { x: piece.pos.x, y: piece.pos.y },\n    to: { x, y },\n    capturedPieceId: target ? target.id : null,\n  });\n}\n\nfunction pseudoMovesForPiece(board, piece) {\n  const moves = [];\n  const { x, y } = piece.pos;\n\n  switch (piece.type) {\n    case PieceType.ROOK: {\n      const dirs = [[1, 0], [-1, 0], [0, 1], [0, -1]];\n      for (const [dx, dy] of dirs) {\n        let cx = x + dx;\n        let cy = y + dy;\n        while (isInsideBoard(cx, cy)) {\n          const target = getPieceAt(board, cx, cy);\n          if (!target) {\n            addMove(board, piece, cx, cy, moves);\n          } else {\n            if (target.side !== piece.side) addMove(board, piece, cx, cy, moves);\n            break;\n          }\n          cx += dx;\n          cy += dy;\n        }\n      }\n      break;\n    }\n    case PieceType.HORSE: {\n      const candidates = [\n        { dx: 2, dy: 1, leg: { x: x + 1, y } },\n        { dx: 2, dy: -1, leg: { x: x + 1, y } },\n        { dx: -2, dy: 1, leg: { x: x - 1, y } },\n        { dx: -2, dy: -1, leg: { x: x - 1, y } },\n        { dx: 1, dy: 2, leg: { x, y: y + 1 } },\n        { dx: -1, dy: 2, leg: { x, y: y + 1 } },\n        { dx: 1, dy: -2, leg: { x, y: y - 1 } },\n        { dx: -1, dy: -2, leg: { x, y: y - 1 } },\n      ];\n      for (const c of candidates) {\n        if (!getPieceAt(board, c.leg.x, c.leg.y)) addMove(board, piece, x + c.dx, y + c.dy, moves);\n      }\n      break;\n    }\n    case PieceType.ELEPHANT: {\n      const candidates = [\n        { dx: 2, dy: 2, eye: { x: x + 1, y: y + 1 } },\n        { dx: 2, dy: -2, eye: { x: x + 1, y: y - 1 } },\n        { dx: -2, dy: 2, eye: { x: x - 1, y: y + 1 } },\n        { dx: -2, dy: -2, eye: { x: x - 1, y: y - 1 } },\n      ];\n      for (const c of candidates) {\n        const nx = x + c.dx;\n        const ny = y + c.dy;\n        if (!isInsideBoard(nx, ny)) continue;\n        if (piece.side === Side.RED && ny < 5) continue;\n        if (piece.side === Side.BLACK && ny > 4) continue;\n        if (!getPieceAt(board, c.eye.x, c.eye.y)) addMove(board, piece, nx, ny, moves);\n      }\n      break;\n    }\n    case PieceType.ADVISOR: {\n      for (const [dx, dy] of [[1, 1], [1, -1], [-1, 1], [-1, -1]]) {\n        const nx = x + dx;\n        const ny = y + dy;\n        if (isInsideBoard(nx, ny) && inPalace(piece.side, nx, ny)) addMove(board, piece, nx, ny, moves);\n      }\n      break;\n    }\n    case PieceType.GENERAL: {\n      for (const [dx, dy] of [[1, 0], [-1, 0], [0, 1], [0, -1]]) {\n        const nx = x + dx;\n        const ny = y + dy;\n        if (isInsideBoard(nx, ny) && inPalace(piece.side, nx, ny)) addMove(board, piece, nx, ny, moves);\n      }\n      const enemy = getGeneral(board, oppositeSide(piece.side));\n      if (enemy && enemy.pos.x === x && clearLine(board, piece.pos, enemy.pos)) {\n        addMove(board, piece, enemy.pos.x, enemy.pos.y, moves);\n      }\n      break;\n    }\n    case PieceType.CANNON: {\n      const dirs = [[1, 0], [-1, 0], [0, 1], [0, -1]];\n      for (const [dx, dy] of dirs) {\n        let cx = x + dx;\n        let cy = y + dy;\n        let screenSeen = false;\n        while (isInsideBoard(cx, cy)) {\n          const target = getPieceAt(board, cx, cy);\n          if (!screenSeen) {\n            if (!target) addMove(board, piece, cx, cy, moves);\n            else screenSeen = true;\n          } else if (target) {\n            if (target.side !== piece.side) addMove(board, piece, cx, cy, moves);\n            break;\n          }\n          cx += dx;\n          cy += dy;\n        }\n      }\n      break;\n    }\n    case PieceType.SOLDIER: {\n      addMove(board, piece, x, y + forwardDelta(piece.side), moves);\n      if (crossedRiver(piece.side, y)) {\n        addMove(board, piece, x + 1, y, moves);\n        addMove(board, piece, x - 1, y, moves);\n      }\n      break;\n    }\n    default:\n      break;\n  }\n\n  return moves;\n}\n\nfunction moveLeavesOwnGeneralSafe(board, move, side) {\n  const next = applyMove(board, move);\n  return !isInCheck(next, side);\n}\n\nfunction getLegalMoves(board, side = board.currentSide) {\n  const moves = [];\n  for (const piece of getPiecesBySide(board, side)) {\n    for (const move of pseudoMovesForPiece(board, piece)) {\n      if (moveLeavesOwnGeneralSafe(board, move, side)) moves.push(move);\n    }\n  }\n  return moves;\n}\n\nfunction isSquareAttacked(board, x, y, bySide) {\n  for (const piece of getPiecesBySide(board, bySide)) {\n    const { x: px, y: py } = piece.pos;\n    switch (piece.type) {\n      case PieceType.ROOK:\n        if ((px === x || py === y) && clearLine(board, piece.pos, { x, y })) return true;\n        break;\n      case PieceType.HORSE: {\n        const dx = Math.abs(px - x);\n        const dy = Math.abs(py - y);\n        if ((dx === 1 && dy === 2 && !getPieceAt(board, px, py + (y > py ? 1 : -1))) ||\n            (dx === 2 && dy === 1 && !getPieceAt(board, px + (x > px ? 1 : -1), py))) return true;\n        break;\n      }\n      case PieceType.ELEPHANT: {\n        const dx = Math.abs(px - x);\n        const dy = Math.abs(py - y);\n        if (dx === 2 && dy === 2) {\n          if (piece.side === Side.RED && y < 5) break;\n          if (piece.side === Side.BLACK && y > 4) break;\n          const eye = { x: (px + x) / 2, y: (py + y) / 2 };\n          if (!getPieceAt(board, eye.x, eye.y)) return true;\n        }\n        break;\n      }\n      case PieceType.ADVISOR:\n        if (Math.abs(px - x) === 1 && Math.abs(py - y) === 1 && inPalace(piece.side, x, y)) return true;\n        break;\n      case PieceType.GENERAL:\n        if (Math.abs(px - x) + Math.abs(py - y) === 1 && inPalace(piece.side, x, y)) return true;\n        if (px === x) {\n          const targetGeneral = getGeneral(board, oppositeSide(piece.side));\n          if (targetGeneral && targetGeneral.pos.x === x && targetGeneral.pos.y === y && clearLine(board, piece.pos, targetGeneral.pos)) return true;\n        }\n        break;\n      case PieceType.CANNON:\n        if ((px === x || py === y) && countBetween(board, piece.pos, { x, y }) === 1) return true;\n        break;\n      case PieceType.SOLDIER: {\n        const dir = forwardDelta(piece.side);\n        if (px === x && py + dir === y) return true;\n        if (crossedRiver(piece.side, py) && py === y && (px + 1 === x || px - 1 === x)) return true;\n        break;\n      }\n      default:\n        break;\n    }\n  }\n  return false;\n}\n\nfunction isInCheck(board, side) {\n  const general = getGeneral(board, side);\n  if (!general) return true;\n  return isSquareAttacked(board, general.pos.x, general.pos.y, oppositeSide(side));\n}\n\nfunction advanceGame(board, move) {\n  const next = cloneBoard(board);\n  const piece = next.pieces.find((p) => p.id === move.pieceId && p.alive);\n  const target = getPieceAt(next, move.to.x, move.to.y);\n  if (target) target.alive = false;\n  piece.pos = { x: move.to.x, y: move.to.y };\n  next.lastMove = { pieceId: piece.id, from: { ...move.from }, to: { ...move.to }, capturedPieceId: target ? target.id : null };\n  next.moveHistory = [...next.moveHistory, next.lastMove];\n  next.currentSide = oppositeSide(board.currentSide);\n  next.selectedPieceId = null;\n\n  const sideToMove = next.currentSide;\n  const legalMoves = getLegalMoves(next, sideToMove);\n  if (legalMoves.length === 0) {\n    if (isInCheck(next, sideToMove)) {\n      next.status = 'checkmate';\n      next.winner = oppositeSide(sideToMove);\n    } else {\n      next.status = 'draw';\n      next.winner = null;\n    }\n  } else if (isInCheck(next, sideToMove)) {\n    next.status = 'check';\n    next.winner = null;\n  } else {\n    next.status = 'playing';\n    next.winner = null;\n  }\n  return next;\n}\n\nconst PIECE_LABELS = {\n  red: {\n    rook: '车', horse: '马', elephant: '相', advisor: '仕', general: '帅', cannon: '炮', soldier: '兵',\n  },\n  black: {\n    rook: '车', horse: '马', elephant: '象', advisor: '士', general: '将', cannon: '炮', soldier: '卒',\n  },\n};\n\nfunction pieceLabel(piece) {\n  return PIECE_LABELS[piece.side][piece.type] || '?';\n}\n\nfunction searchBestMove(board, { side = board.currentSide, depth = 1, timeLimitMs = 60 } = {}) {\n  const legal = getLegalMoves(board, side);\n  if (!legal.length) return null;\n\n  let bestMove = legal[0];\n  let bestScore = -Infinity;\n  for (const move of legal) {\n    const next = advanceGame(board, move);\n    let score = 0;\n    if (move.capturedPieceId) score += 1000;\n    if (next.status === 'checkmate') score += 99999;\n    if (next.status === 'check') score += 30;\n    if (move.pieceId.includes('r') && move.to.y < move.from.y) score += 1;\n    if (score > bestScore) {\n      bestScore = score;\n      bestMove = move;\n    }\n  }\n  return bestMove;\n}\n\nfunction replayMoves(initialBoard, moves) {\n  return moves.reduce((board, move) => advanceGame(board, move), initialBoard);\n}\n\nmodule.exports = {\n  BOARD_WIDTH,\n  BOARD_HEIGHT,\n  Side,\n  PieceType,\n  oppositeSide,\n  isInsideBoard,\n  createInitialBoard,\n  cloneBoard,\n  getPieceAt,\n  getLegalMoves,\n  isInCheck,\n  advanceGame,\n  searchBestMove,\n  pieceLabel,\n  replayMoves,\n};\nEOF\ncat > \"$BASE/miniprogram/utils/game-state.js\" <<'EOF'\nfunction createGameState() {\n  return {\n    mode: 'ai',\n    side: 'red',\n    status: 'ready',\n    winner: null,\n    moveCount: 0,\n    message: '准备开始',\n  };\n}\n\nmodule.exports = { createGameState };\nEOF\ncat > \"$BASE/miniprogram/pages/game/game.js\" <<'EOF'\nconst { createGameState } = require('../../utils/game-state');\nconst {\n  Side,\n  createInitialBoard,\n  cloneBoard,\n  getPieceAt,\n  getLegalMoves,\n  advanceGame,\n  searchBestMove,\n  pieceLabel,\n} = require('../../utils/chess-engine');\n\nfunction coordKey(x, y) {\n  return `${x}:${y}`;\n}\n\nfunction buildBoardView(board, selectedPieceId, legalMoves) {\n  const legalMap = new Set(legalMoves.map((move) => coordKey(move.to.x, move.to.y)));\n  const lastMoveMap = board.lastMove\n    ? new Set([coordKey(board.lastMove.from.x, board.lastMove.from.y), coordKey(board.lastMove.to.x, board.lastMove.to.y)])\n    : new Set();\n\n  const rows = [];\n  for (let y = 0; y < 10; y += 1) {\n    const cells = [];\n    for (let x = 0; x < 9; x += 1) {\n      const piece = getPieceAt(board, x, y);\n      const selected = piece && piece.id === selectedPieceId;\n      const legalTarget = legalMap.has(coordKey(x, y));\n      const lastMove = lastMoveMap.has(coordKey(x, y));\n      cells.push({\n        x,\n        y,\n        key: coordKey(x, y),\n        piece,\n        text: piece ? pieceLabel(piece) : '',\n        selected,\n        legalTarget,\n        lastMove,\n      });\n    }\n    rows.push({ y, cells });\n  }\n  return rows;\n}\n\nPage({\n  data: {\n    state: createGameState(),\n    board: createInitialBoard(),\n    boardRows: [],\n    selectedPieceId: null,\n    legalMoves: [],\n    tips: [\n      '点棋子选中，再点可落位置',\n      '红方先手，目前默认人机对战',\n      '后续可继续接入悔棋、提示、复盘'\n    ],\n  },\n\n  onLoad() {\n    this.boardHistory = [];\n    this.aiTimer = null;\n    this.refreshBoard('游戏页已就绪');\n  },\n\n  onUnload() {\n    if (this.aiTimer) clearTimeout(this.aiTimer);\n  },\n\n  refreshBoard(message) {\n    const legalMoves = getLegalMoves(this.data.board, this.data.board.currentSide);\n    const boardRows = buildBoardView(this.data.board, this.data.selectedPieceId, this.data.legalMoves);\n    const summary = this.getStatusText(this.data.board, message);\n    this.setData({\n      state: {\n        ...this.data.state,\n        status: this.data.board.status,\n        winner: this.data.board.winner,\n        side: this.data.board.currentSide,\n        moveCount: this.data.board.moveHistory.length,\n        message: summary,\n      },\n      boardRows,\n      legalMoves,\n      boardLabel: summary,\n    });\n  },\n\n  getStatusText(board, fallback) {\n    if (board.status === 'checkmate') {\n      return board.winner === Side.RED ? '红方胜，已将死' : '黑方胜，已将死';\n    }\n    if (board.status === 'draw') return '平局';\n    if (board.status === 'check') return `${board.currentSide === Side.RED ? '红方' : '黑方'}被将军`;\n    return fallback || `${board.currentSide === Side.RED ? '红方' : '黑方'}走子`;\n  },\n\n  resetGame() {\n    if (this.aiTimer) clearTimeout(this.aiTimer);\n    this.boardHistory = [];\n    this.setData({\n      board: createInitialBoard(),\n      selectedPieceId: null,\n      legalMoves: [],\n    });\n    this.refreshBoard('对局已重开');\n  },\n\n  undoMove() {\n    if (!this.boardHistory || !this.boardHistory.length) return;\n    if (this.aiTimer) clearTimeout(this.aiTimer);\n    const previous = this.boardHistory.pop();\n    this.setData({\n      board: cloneBoard(previous),\n      selectedPieceId: null,\n      legalMoves: [],\n    });\n    this.refreshBoard('已悔棋一步');\n  },\n\n  onCellTap(e) {\n    if (this.data.board.status === 'checkmate' || this.data.board.status === 'draw') return;\n    if (this.data.board.currentSide === Side.BLACK) return;\n\n    const x = Number(e.currentTarget.dataset.x);\n    const y = Number(e.currentTarget.dataset.y);\n    const piece = getPieceAt(this.data.board, x, y);\n    const selectedPieceId = this.data.selectedPieceId;\n    const selectedMoves = this.data.legalMoves;\n    const legalMove = selectedMoves.find((move) => move.to.x === x && move.to.y === y);\n\n    if (legalMove) {\n      this.commitMove(legalMove, '你走了一步');\n      return;\n    }\n\n    if (piece && piece.side === Side.RED && this.data.board.currentSide === Side.RED) {\n      const moves = getLegalMoves(this.data.board, Side.RED).filter((move) => move.pieceId === piece.id);\n      this.setData({\n        selectedPieceId: piece.id,\n        legalMoves: moves,\n      });\n      this.refreshBoard(`${pieceLabel(piece)}已选中`);\n      return;\n    }\n\n    if (selectedPieceId) {\n      this.setData({ selectedPieceId: null, legalMoves: [] });\n      this.refreshBoard('取消选中');\n    }\n  },\n\n  commitMove(move, message) {\n    this.boardHistory.push(cloneBoard(this.data.board));\n    const nextBoard = advanceGame(this.data.board, move);\n    this.setData({\n      board: nextBoard,\n      selectedPieceId: null,\n      legalMoves: [],\n    });\n    this.refreshBoard(message);\n\n    if (nextBoard.status === 'playing' && nextBoard.currentSide === Side.BLACK) {\n      this.scheduleAiMove();\n    }\n  },\n\n  scheduleAiMove() {\n    if (this.aiTimer) clearTimeout(this.aiTimer);\n    this.aiTimer = setTimeout(() => {\n      this.aiTimer = null;\n      const move = searchBestMove(this.data.board, { side: Side.BLACK, depth: 1, timeLimitMs: 80 });\n      if (!move) {\n        this.refreshBoard('AI 无合法走法');\n        return;\n      }\n      this.commitMove(move, 'AI 已落子');\n    }, 180);\n  },\n\n  startGame() {\n    this.resetGame();\n  },\n\n  goResult() {\n    wx.navigateTo({ url: '/pages/result/result' });\n  },\n});\nEOF\ncat > \"$BASE/miniprogram/pages/game/game.wxml\" <<'EOF'\n<view class=\"card\">\n  <view class=\"section-title\">{{state.message}}</view>\n  <view class=\"meta\">模式：{{state.mode}} · 当前：{{state.side}} · 步数：{{state.moveCount}}</view>\n\n  <view class=\"board-shell\">\n    <view class=\"board-grid\">\n      <block wx:for=\"{{boardRows}}\" wx:key=\"y\">\n        <view class=\"board-row\">\n          <block wx:for=\"{{item.cells}}\" wx:key=\"key\">\n            <view\n              class=\"board-cell {{cell.selected ? 'cell-selected' : ''}} {{cell.legalTarget ? 'cell-legal' : ''}} {{cell.lastMove ? 'cell-lastmove' : ''}}\"\n              data-x=\"{{cell.x}}\"\n              data-y=\"{{cell.y}}\"\n              bindtap=\"onCellTap\"\n            >\n              <view wx:if=\"{{cell.legalTarget && !cell.piece}}\" class=\"legal-dot\"></view>\n              <view wx:if=\"{{cell.piece}}\" class=\"piece piece-{{cell.piece.side}} {{cell.selected ? 'piece-selected' : ''}}\">\n                {{cell.text}}\n              </view>\n            </view>\n          </block>\n        </view>\n      </block>\n    </view>\n  </view>\n\n  <view class=\"actions\">\n    <button class=\"button-primary\" bindtap=\"startGame\">重新开始</button>\n    <button bindtap=\"undoMove\">悔棋</button>\n    <button bindtap=\"goResult\">去结算页</button>\n  </view>\n</view>\n\n<view class=\"card\">\n  <view class=\"section-title\">提示</view>\n  <view wx:for=\"{{tips}}\" wx:key=\"*this\">- {{item}}</view>\n</view>\nEOF\ncat > \"$BASE/miniprogram/pages/game/game.wxss\" <<'EOF'\n.section-title { font-size: 32rpx; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 16rpx; }\n.meta { color: #666; margin-bottom: 20rpx; }\n.board-shell {\n  padding: 18rpx;\n  background: #ead9b4;\n  border-radius: 24rpx;\n  margin-bottom: 20rpx;\n}\n.board-grid {\n  background: #f8e8c4;\n  border: 2rpx solid #a07b46;\n  border-radius: 16rpx;\n  overflow: hidden;\n}\n.board-row {\n  display: flex;\n}\n.board-cell {\n  width: 76rpx;\n  height: 76rpx;\n  box-sizing: border-box;\n  border-right: 1rpx solid rgba(160, 123, 70, 0.35);\n  border-bottom: 1rpx solid rgba(160, 123, 70, 0.35);\n  display: flex;\n  align-items: center;\n  justify-content: center;\n  position: relative;\n}\n.board-row:last-child .board-cell { border-bottom: none; }\n.board-cell:last-child { border-right: none; }\n.cell-selected { background: rgba(184, 54, 45, 0.18); }\n.cell-legal { background: rgba(43, 122, 77, 0.12); }\n.cell-lastmove { background: rgba(255, 214, 102, 0.18); }\n.legal-dot {\n  width: 18rpx;\n  height: 18rpx;\n  border-radius: 50%;\n  background: rgba(43, 122, 77, 0.7);\n}\n.piece {\n  width: 58rpx;\n  height: 58rpx;\n  border-radius: 50%;\n  display: flex;\n  align-items: center;\n  justify-content: center;\n  font-size: 30rpx;\n  font-weight: 700;\n  box-shadow: 0 4rpx 10rpx rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.12);\n}\n.piece-red {\n  background: #f8efe2;\n  color: #b8362d;\n  border: 2rpx solid #c06b63;\n}\n.piece-black {\n  background: #f6f1e8;\n  color: #333;\n  border: 2rpx solid #666;\n}\n.piece-selected { transform: scale(1.04); }\n.actions { display: flex; gap: 16rpx; flex-wrap: wrap; }\nbutton { margin-top: 16rpx; }\nEOF\nnpm test --prefix \"$BASE\"","workdir":"/home/gem/workspace/agent/workspace","timeout":120}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"code889","model":"gpt-5.4-mini","usage":{"input":704,"output":12704,"cacheRead":80896,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":94304,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774088880555}}
