{"type":"message","id":"64d1fa3a","parentId":"33a86b40","timestamp":"2026-03-21T13:51:26.686Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Inspecting workspace files**\n\nI need to take a closer look at the workspace files to understand the current state, possibly using a search function. I could implement a WebSocket layer abstraction in the miniprogram/utils and figure out how to integrate it into the game page, with a fallback to the real wx.connectSocket if it's available. I'll check if there are existing project configs and read the current match-protocol, but I might find I've already done this. Getting careful here about not inventing backend stuff is important!\n\n**Creating a WebSocket layer**\n\nI’m considering creating a layer for connecting, disconnecting, and sending messages, which I could integrate into the page with a demo endpoint and manual URL input. Maybe adding a config file for the WebSocket URL and maintaining a state on the page would be helpful. I realize this might require actual WebSocket client implementation in the mini program, even if it’s just a placeholder. I could implement this in miniprogram/utils/match-transport.js, using wx.connectSocket and providing methods to connect, close, and send envelopes.\n\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_C7wm9WxGmJd2zHLFwW6U9Qd0","name":"memory_search","arguments":{"maxResults":5,"minScore":0.2,"query":"中国象棋 微信小游戏 在线匹配 WebSocket 信令层 小程序 连接层 match-protocol match-transport"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"code889","model":"gpt-5.4-mini","usage":{"input":875,"output":1087,"cacheRead":73728,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":75690,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774101066188}}
