{"type":"message","id":"5e370bf7","parentId":"f9ffd566","timestamp":"2026-03-21T13:51:54.552Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Planning WebSocket Integration**\n\nI need to continue implementing the WebSocket or signaling layer carefully, ensuring no external connections. I could create an abstraction with a simulated mock transport and a real wx.connectSocket adapter, although that might not be testable. I likely need to update the mini program to use this and inspect the rest of game.js. I might create a new utils/transport.js. Additionally, I should look into existing tests and consider writing unit tests for the transport layer. I'll plan to create match-transport.js and relevant adapters.\n\n**Reviewing Game.js Integration**\n\nI need to read the remaining part of game.js, specifically from offset 261, to examine the functions towards the end and identify potential integration points. It’s essential to understand how everything fits together! By doing this, I can ensure that I'm not missing any critical details that could impact the overall functionality. It's always good to have a comprehensive view, so I'll take my time to analyze this section carefully.\n\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_Ag6a3LWj9dB7m52uw1Yk69aW","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/gem/workspace/agent/workspace/chinese-chess-minigame/miniprogram/pages/game/game.js","limit":220,"offset":261,"path":"/home/gem/workspace/agent/workspace/chinese-chess-minigame/miniprogram/pages/game/game.js"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_jDkEFLysFwLBM5GSZzmW7UdR","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/gem/workspace/agent/workspace/chinese-chess-minigame/test/match.test.js","limit":260,"offset":1,"path":"/home/gem/workspace/agent/workspace/chinese-chess-minigame/test/match.test.js"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"code889","model":"gpt-5.4-mini","usage":{"input":5044,"output":606,"cacheRead":74240,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":79890,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774101101639}}
{"type":"message","id":"4b11d28d","parentId":"5e370bf7","timestamp":"2026-03-21T13:51:54.565Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_Ag6a3LWj9dB7m52uw1Yk69aW","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"    const stepsToUndo = this.data.state.mode === 'ai' && this.data.board.currentSide === Side.RED ? 2 : 1;\n    let previous = null;\n    for (let i = 0; i < stepsToUndo; i += 1) {\n      if (!this.boardHistory.length) break;\n      previous = this.boardHistory.pop();\n    }\n    if (!previous) return;\n\n    this.setData({\n      board: cloneBoard(previous),\n      selectedPieceId: null,\n      legalMoves: [],\n      hintMove: null,\n      hintText: stepsToUndo === 2 ? '已悔棋两步，轮到你重新落子' : '已悔棋一步',\n    });\n    this.refreshBoard(stepsToUndo === 2 ? '已悔棋两步' : '已悔棋一步');\n  },\n\n  showHint() {\n    if (this.data.board.status === 'checkmate' || this.data.board.status === 'draw') {\n      this.setData({ hintMove: null, hintText: '对局已结束，无法提示' });\n      this.refreshBoard('对局已结束');\n      return;\n    }\n    if (this.data.board.currentSide !== Side.RED) {\n      this.setData({ hintMove: null, hintText: '当前轮到黑方，先等 AI 走完' });\n      this.refreshBoard('当前轮到黑方');\n      return;\n    }\n\n    const hintMove = searchBestMove(this.data.board, { side: Side.RED, depth: 2, timeLimitMs: 60 });\n    if (!hintMove) {\n      this.setData({ hintMove: null, hintText: '当前没有可用提示' });\n      this.refreshBoard('当前没有可用提示');\n      return;\n    }\n\n    const piece = getPieceAt(this.data.board, hintMove.from.x, hintMove.from.y);\n    const hintText = `${piece ? pieceLabel(piece) : '棋子'} 建议走 ${formatCoord(hintMove.from)} → ${formatCoord(hintMove.to)}`;\n    this.setData({\n      hintMove,\n      hintText,\n      selectedPieceId: piece ? piece.id : null,\n      legalMoves: getLegalMoves(this.data.board, Side.RED).filter((move) => move.pieceId === hintMove.pieceId),\n    });\n    this.refreshBoard('已给出提示', this.data.legalMoves, hintMove);\n  },\n\n  onCellTap(e) {\n    if (this.data.board.status === 'checkmate' || this.data.board.status === 'draw') return;\n    if (this.data.board.currentSide === Side.BLACK) return;\n\n    const x = Number(e.currentTarget.dataset.x);\n    const y = Number(e.currentTarget.dataset.y);\n    const piece = getPieceAt(this.data.board, x, y);\n    const selectedPieceId = this.data.selectedPieceId;\n    const selectedMoves = this.data.legalMoves;\n    const legalMove = selectedMoves.find((move) => move.to.x === x && move.to.y === y);\n\n    if (legalMove) {\n      this.commitMove(legalMove, '你走了一步');\n      return;\n    }\n\n    if (piece && piece.side === Side.RED && this.data.board.currentSide === Side.RED) {\n      const moves = getLegalMoves(this.data.board, Side.RED).filter((move) => move.pieceId === piece.id);\n      this.setData({\n        selectedPieceId: piece.id,\n        legalMoves: moves,\n        hintMove: null,\n        hintText: `已选中 ${pieceLabel(piece)}，可落点已高亮`,\n      });\n      this.refreshBoard(`${pieceLabel(piece)}已选中`, moves, null);\n      return;\n    }\n\n    if (selectedPieceId) {\n      this.setData({ selectedPieceId: null, legalMoves: [], hintMove: null, hintText: '已取消选中' });\n      this.refreshBoard('取消选中', [], null);\n    }\n  },\n\n  finishIfNeeded(nextBoard) {\n    if (nextBoard.status === 'playing') return false;\n    this.saveMatchResult(nextBoard);\n    const resultUrl = `/pages/result/result?status=${nextBoard.status}&winner=${nextBoard.winner || ''}`;\n    wx.reLaunch({ url: resultUrl });\n    return true;\n  },\n\n  commitMove(move, message) {\n    this.boardHistory.push(cloneBoard(this.data.board));\n    const nextBoard = advanceGame(this.data.board, move);\n    this.setData({\n      board: nextBoard,\n      selectedPieceId: null,\n      legalMoves: [],\n      hintMove: null,\n      hintText: message,\n    });\n    this.refreshBoard(message, [], null);\n\n    if (this.finishIfNeeded(nextBoard)) return;\n\n    if (nextBoard.status === 'playing' && nextBoard.currentSide === Side.BLACK) {\n      this.scheduleAiMove();\n    }\n  },\n\n  scheduleAiMove() {\n    if (this.aiTimer) clearTimeout(this.aiTimer);\n    this.aiTimer = setTimeout(() => {\n      this.aiTimer = null;\n      const move = searchBestMove(this.data.board, { side: Side.BLACK, depth: 1, timeLimitMs: 80 });\n      if (!move) {\n        this.setData({ hintMove: null, hintText: 'AI 无合法走法' });\n        this.refreshBoard('AI 无合法走法');\n        return;\n      }\n      this.commitMove(move, 'AI 已落子');\n    }, 180);\n  },\n\n  startGame() {\n    this.resetGame();\n  },\n\n  goResult() {\n    wx.navigateTo({ url: '/pages/result/result' });\n  },\n});\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774101114556}}
{"type":"message","id":"d5fd600f","parentId":"4b11d28d","timestamp":"2026-03-21T13:51:54.576Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_jDkEFLysFwLBM5GSZzmW7UdR","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"import assert from 'node:assert/strict';\nimport test from 'node:test';\nimport {\n  MatchEventType,\n  MatchMode,\n  MatchState,\n  Side,\n  applyMatchEvent,\n  canSendMove,\n  createAckEvent,\n  createDrawOfferEvent,\n  createMatchAccept,\n  createMatchRequest,\n  createMatchRoom,\n  createMoveEvent,\n  createResignEvent,\n  createSyncEvent,\n  describeMatchRoom,\n  isProtocolEnvelope,\n} from '../src/index.js';\n\ntest('match protocol creates a valid request envelope', () => {\n  const envelope = createMatchRequest({ roomId: 'room-1', senderId: 'u-red', desiredSide: Side.RED, seed: 42 });\n  assert.equal(isProtocolEnvelope(envelope), true);\n  assert.equal(envelope.type, MatchEventType.REQUEST);\n  assert.equal(envelope.payload.desiredSide, Side.RED);\n});\n\ntest('match protocol transitions request -> accept -> move', () => {\n  const room = createMatchRoom({ roomId: 'room-1', selfId: 'u-red', selfSide: Side.RED, mode: MatchMode.ONLINE });\n  const requested = applyMatchEvent(room, createMatchRequest({ roomId: 'room-1', senderId: 'u-red', desiredSide: Side.RED }));\n  assert.equal(requested.state, MatchState.MATCHING);\n\n  const playing = applyMatchEvent(requested, createMatchAccept({ roomId: 'room-1', senderId: 'u-black', opponentId: 'u-black', selfSide: Side.RED }));\n  assert.equal(playing.state, MatchState.PLAYING);\n  assert.equal(canSendMove(playing), true);\n\n  const moved = applyMatchEvent(playing, createMoveEvent({ roomId: 'room-1', senderId: 'u-red', move: { pieceId: 'r-r1', from: { x: 0, y: 9 }, to: { x: 0, y: 8 } }, seq: 1 }));\n  assert.equal(moved.sequence, 2);\n  assert.equal(moved.turn, Side.BLACK);\n  assert.equal(moved.moveLog.length, 1);\n});\n\ntest('match protocol supports sync, ack, draw and resign flows', () => {\n  let room = createMatchRoom({ roomId: 'room-2', selfId: 'u-red', selfSide: Side.RED, mode: MatchMode.ONLINE, state: MatchState.PLAYING });\n  room = applyMatchEvent(room, createSyncEvent({ roomId: 'room-2', senderId: 'u-black', board: { snapshot: true }, turn: Side.RED, moveSeq: 7 }));\n  assert.equal(room.state, MatchState.SYNCHRONIZING);\n  assert.equal(room.sequence, 7);\n\n  room = applyMatchEvent(room, createAckEvent({ roomId: 'room-2', senderId: 'u-black', ackSeq: 7 }));\n  assert.equal(room.lastAckSeq, 7);\n\n  room = applyMatchEvent(room, createDrawOfferEvent({ roomId: 'room-2', senderId: 'u-black' }));\n  assert.equal(room.pendingDraw, true);\n\n  room = applyMatchEvent(room, createResignEvent({ roomId: 'room-2', senderId: 'u-black' }));\n  assert.equal(room.state, MatchState.FINISHED);\n  assert.equal(room.result.reason, 'resign');\n  assert.equal(room.result.winner, Side.RED);\n});\n\ntest('describeMatchRoom summarizes state cleanly', () => {\n  const room = createMatchRoom({ roomId: 'room-3', selfId: 'u-red', selfSide: Side.RED });\n  const summary = describeMatchRoom(room);\n  assert.deepEqual(summary.roomId, 'room-3');\n  assert.equal(summary.state, MatchState.IDLE);\n  assert.equal(summary.selfSide, Side.RED);\n});\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774101114568}}
{"type":"message","id":"babf7712","parentId":"d5fd600f","timestamp":"2026-03-21T13:52:45.331Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Inspecting game files**\n\nI need to take a closer look at the existing game.js, especially towards the bottom, to make sure the results or tutorials remain unaffected. I’m considering writing new files and possibly modifying game.js and app.js, maybe adding to the app's globalData with signalingUrl. However, I don’t think I’ll need to add anything to app.json. Also, I have to ensure that there are tests for the pure functions of transport.\n\n**Developing the transport module**\n\nI need to write a module that includes tests for envelope parsing and a fake socket factory. I could create a test file for this in Node, using a stub socket object. \n\nThen I'll integrate it into game.js with functions like `initTransport` and `connectSignal`. Since there are already many methods on the page, I’ll add new methods and data fields. I’m thinking of crafting a match-transport module in CommonJS using an event emitter without external libraries. I'll also implement a callback registry for its behavior.\n\n**Considering controller implementation**\n\nI think a separate controller would be really beneficial! It would help manage the room state through `applyMatchEvent` and transport status with `createMatchTransport`. I’m thinking of adding methods like `connect(url)`, `disconnect`, `sendMove(move)`, and `sendHeartbeat`, which could effectively link the protocol to the websocket layer. Implementing `createMatchSignalClient({room, url, adapter, onStateChange, onRoomChange})` could make it easier for the game page to use directly. It might add more code, but I believe it's manageable.\n\n**Considering board synchronization**\n\nI'm thinking about incorporating board synchronization by detecting incoming `match.move` events. If the `envelope.payload.move` exists, I might need to create a function to apply the remote move to the game board. I'll use `advanceGame` to ensure the move follows rules and the current player's turn matches. If the game page is online and receives an opponent's move while the match is ongoing, it should apply the move accordingly. It looks like the game page will manage event processing for the board.\n\n**Integrating remote envelope handling**\n\nI'm considering introducing a set of methods like `applyRemoteEnvelope(envelope)` within the page, utilizing `applyMatchEvent` and `advanceGame`. I want to avoid overengineering this, so I'll keep the transport module alongside basic page integration for handshake and remote envelope handling. Since there's no actual server, the code will still be functional. I need to inspect if any utilities can be used in the page, but it looks like there aren't any. I'll add `match-session` while keeping it minimal.\n\n**Considering move events**\n\nI’m thinking about how to handle moves in a game. When the local player makes a move, I should send a move event if connected online after the board changes. For accepting requests, using connect buttons for those operations might be better since they are just demos. However, using client wrappers could simplify things, and perhaps it's best for the local page to utilize the signal client `this.signalClient` upon connection.\n\n**Planning interaction buttons**\n\nI’m considering adding buttons like `发送同步`, `发送心跳`, `发送提和`, `发送认输`, and maybe `发送当前落子`. But the actual move is local to the game. I still need a client module that can send `createEnvelope` events and handle incoming JSON. It’s interesting to think about how this will all work together to create smooth interactions for the user! Let’s ensure each button has the right function to enhance the experience.\n\n**Considering file modification**\n\nI’m thinking that since game.js is long, it might be a good idea to rewrite the whole file with the current content plus any modifications. Using a script is an option since Node is available. I wonder if I could create a small Node script to handle the transformation? However, using `cat > file` manually could work too, though it needs accuracy. Maybe using Perl for a more targeted programmatic modification would be safer in this case.\n\n**Considering file versioning and integration**\n\nI think it's best to write an entirely new version of the file based on the current content we've read. This will allow me to compose with modifications without getting too tangled up. While it might be lengthy, it feels manageable. I need to ensure the syntax is valid. The user specifically asked to connect the existing abstraction to a WebSocket layer, so I should create a game page that minimally integrates connection status and buttons. I'll set up a new game.js for handling transport and match room management.\n\n**Defining signal client setup**\n\nI’m thinking about setting up the signal client at the top with this code:  \n```  \nconst { createMatchSignalClient, buildWxSocketAdapter } = require('../../utils/match-signal');  \n```  \nThen in the onLoad function, I’ll create `signalClient` with necessary configurations and handlers. I need `handleRoomUpdate` to manage room persistence and connection status. Additionally, `handleRemoteEnvelope` will handle actions like MOVE and SYNC on the board. I'll check the envelope and update the board accordingly. Using `setData` inside those callbacks will help ensure everything stays in sync. It seems straightforward!\n\n**Implementing remote move functionality**\n\nI’m working on the `applyRemoteMove` method, which will look something like this:  \n```  \napplyRemoteMove(move, envelope) {  \n  const legalMove = advanceGame(this.data.board, move);  \n  this.setData({...});  \n  this.refreshBoard('收到对方走子', [], null, this.data.syncMarkers);  \n  if (finishIfNeeded(nextBoard)) { ... }  \n}  \n```  \nHowever, if the board isn’t in the right state, I could encounter an error. I think it’s a good idea to set an error text for those cases, so the user knows what’s happening. I’ll have to keep that in mind!\n\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_qSVDgxI7Ab0YW7X3w93bKimR","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"const {\n  MatchEventType,\n  createAckEvent,\n  createDrawOfferEvent,\n  createDrawResponseEvent,\n  createErrorEvent,\n  createHeartbeatEvent,\n  createMatchRoom,\n  createMoveEvent,\n  createResignEvent,\n  createSyncEvent,\n  isProtocolEnvelope,\n  applyMatchEvent,\n} = require('./match-protocol');\n\nconst TransportStatus = Object.freeze({\n  IDLE: 'idle',\n  CONNECTING: 'connecting',\n  OPEN: 'open',\n  CLOSING: 'closing',\n  CLOSED: 'closed',\n  ERROR: 'error',\n});\n\nfunction safeJsonParse(raw) {\n  if (raw && typeof raw === 'object') return raw;\n  if (typeof raw !== 'string') return null;\n  try {\n    return JSON.parse(raw);\n  } catch (error) {\n    return null;\n  }\n}\n\nfunction buildWxSocketAdapter(wxApi = typeof wx !== 'undefined' ? wx : null) {\n  if (!wxApi || typeof wxApi.connectSocket !== 'function') {\n    throw new Error('wx socket API is unavailable');\n  }\n\n  return {\n    open(url, handlers = {}) {\n      const task = wxApi.connectSocket({ url });\n      const bind = (method, handler) => {\n        if (task && typeof task[method] === 'function') task[method](handler);\n      };\n\n      bind('onOpen', (event) => handlers.onOpen && handlers.onOpen(event));\n      bind('onClose', (event) => handlers.onClose && handlers.onClose(event));\n      bind('onError', (event) => handlers.onError && handlers.onError(event));\n      bind('onMessage', (event) => handlers.onMessage && handlers.onMessage(event.data));\n\n      return {\n        send(data) {\n          wxApi.sendSocketMessage({\n            data,\n            success: (res) => handlers.onSendSuccess && handlers.onSendSuccess(res),\n            fail: (err) => handlers.onSendError && handlers.onSendError(err),\n          });\n        },\n        close(code = 1000, reason = 'client close') {\n          if (typeof wxApi.closeSocket === 'function') {\n            wxApi.closeSocket({ code, reason });\n          }\n        },\n      };\n    },\n  };\n}\n\nfunction createMatchSignalClient({\n  room = createMatchRoom(),\n  url = '',\n  adapter = null,\n  onRoomChange = null,\n  onTransportChange = null,\n  onEnvelope = null,\n  onError = null,\n} = {}) {\n  const listeners = {\n    roomChange: onRoomChange,\n    transportChange: onTransportChange,\n    envelope: onEnvelope,\n    error: onError,\n  };\n\n  let transport = null;\n  let transportState = {\n    status: TransportStatus.IDLE,\n    url,\n    lastError: null,\n    connectedAt: null,\n    closedAt: null,\n    lastMessageAt: null,\n  };\n  let roomState = room;\n\n  const socketAdapter = adapter || (typeof wx !== 'undefined' ? buildWxSocketAdapter(wx) : null);\n\n  function emit(kind, payload, extra) {\n    const handler = listeners[kind];\n    if (typeof handler === 'function') handler(payload, extra);\n  }\n\n  function setTransportState(patch) {\n    transportState = { ...transportState, ...patch };\n    emit('transportChange', transportState, clientApi);\n  }\n\n  function setRoomState(nextRoom, envelope = null) {\n    roomState = nextRoom;\n    emit('roomChange', roomState, envelope, clientApi);\n  }\n\n  function handleEnvelope(envelope) {\n    if (!isProtocolEnvelope(envelope)) {\n      const error = { code: 'INVALID_ENVELOPE', message: 'not a valid protocol envelope', raw: envelope };\n      setTransportState({ status: TransportStatus.ERROR, lastError: error });\n      emit('error', error, clientApi);\n      return;\n    }\n\n    const nextRoom = applyMatchEvent(roomState, envelope);\n    setRoomState(nextRoom, envelope);\n    setTransportState({ lastMessageAt: envelope.ts || Date.now(), lastError: null });\n    emit('envelope', envelope, clientApi);\n  }\n\n  const clientApi = {\n    getTransportState: () => transportState,\n    getRoom: () => roomState,\n    setHandlers(nextHandlers = {}) {\n      Object.assign(listeners, nextHandlers);\n      return clientApi;\n    },\n    connect(nextUrl = transportState.url) {\n      if (!socketAdapter) {\n        const error = { code: 'ADAPTER_MISSING', message: 'socket adapter is unavailable' };\n        setTransportState({ status: TransportStatus.ERROR, lastError: error });\n        emit('error', error, clientApi);\n        return false;\n      }\n      if (!nextUrl) {\n        const error = { code: 'EMPTY_URL', message: 'signaling url is empty' };\n        setTransportState({ status: TransportStatus.ERROR, lastError: error });\n        emit('error', error, clientApi);\n        return false;\n      }\n\n      if (transport) {\n        clientApi.disconnect();\n      }\n\n      setTransportState({ status: TransportStatus.CONNECTING, url: nextUrl, lastError: null });\n      transport = socketAdapter.open(nextUrl, {\n        onOpen() {\n          setTransportState({ status: TransportStatus.OPEN, connectedAt: Date.now(), lastError: null });\n        },\n        onMessage(raw) {\n          const parsed = safeJsonParse(raw);\n          if (!parsed) {\n            const error = { code: 'PARSE_ERROR', message: 'message is not valid JSON', raw };\n            setTransportState({ status: TransportStatus.ERROR, lastError: error });\n            emit('error', error, clientApi);\n            return;\n          }\n          handleEnvelope(parsed);\n        },\n        onClose(event) {\n          setTransportState({ status: TransportStatus.CLOSED, closedAt: Date.now(), lastError: null, closeEvent: event || null });\n          transport = null;\n        },\n        onError(event) {\n          const error = { code: 'SOCKET_ERROR', message: 'socket error', event: event || null };\n          setTransportState({ status: TransportStatus.ERROR, lastError: error });\n          emit('error', error, clientApi);\n        },\n        onSendError(err) {\n          const error = { code: 'SEND_ERROR', message: 'failed to send socket message', event: err || null };\n          setTransportState({ status: TransportStatus.ERROR, lastError: error });\n          emit('error', error, clientApi);\n        },\n      });\n\n      return true;\n    },\n    disconnect() {\n      if (!transport) {\n        setTransportState({ status: TransportStatus.CLOSED, closedAt: Date.now() });\n        return true;\n      }\n      setTransportState({ status: TransportStatus.CLOSING });\n      try {\n        transport.close();\n      } finally {\n        transport = null;\n        setTransportState({ status: TransportStatus.CLOSED, closedAt: Date.now() });\n      }\n      return true;\n    },\n    sendEnvelope(envelope) {\n      if (!transport || transportState.status !== TransportStatus.OPEN) return false;\n      transport.send(JSON.stringify(envelope));\n      return true;\n    },\n    sendMove(move, meta = {}) {\n      return clientApi.sendEnvelope(createMoveEvent({ roomId: roomState.roomId, senderId: roomState.selfId, move, seq: meta.seq || roomState.sequence }));\n    },\n    sendAck(ackSeq, hash = null) {\n      return clientApi.sendEnvelope(createAckEvent({ roomId: roomState.roomId, senderId: roomState.selfId, ackSeq, hash }));\n    },\n    sendSync(board, turn, moveSeq = 0) {\n      return clientApi.sendEnvelope(createSyncEvent({ roomId: roomState.roomId, senderId: roomState.selfId, board, turn, moveSeq }));\n    },\n    sendHeartbeat(ping = Date.now()) {\n      return clientApi.sendEnvelope(createHeartbeatEvent({ roomId: roomState.roomId, senderId: roomState.selfId, ping }));\n    },\n    sendDrawOffer() {\n      return clientApi.sendEnvelope(createDrawOfferEvent({ roomId: roomState.roomId, senderId: roomState.selfId }));\n    },\n    sendDrawResponse(accepted = false) {\n      return clientApi.sendEnvelope(createDrawResponseEvent({ roomId: roomState.roomId, senderId: roomState.selfId, accepted }));\n    },\n    sendResign() {\n      return clientApi.sendEnvelope(createResignEvent({ roomId: roomState.roomId, senderId: roomState.selfId }));\n    },\n    sendError(code, message) {\n      return clientApi.sendEnvelope(createErrorEvent({ roomId: roomState.roomId, senderId: roomState.selfId, code, message }));\n    },\n    ingest(raw) {\n      const parsed = safeJsonParse(raw);\n      if (!parsed) return false;\n      handleEnvelope(parsed);\n      return true;\n    },\n    applyIncomingEnvelope(envelope) {\n      handleEnvelope(envelope);\n      return roomState;\n    },\n    dispose() {\n      clientApi.disconnect();\n    },\n  };\n\n  return clientApi;\n}\n\nmodule.exports = {\n  TransportStatus,\n  safeJsonParse,\n  buildWxSocketAdapter,\n  createMatchSignalClient,\n};\n","file_path":"/home/gem/workspace/agent/workspace/chinese-chess-minigame/miniprogram/utils/match-signal.js","path":"/home/gem/workspace/agent/workspace/chinese-chess-minigame/miniprogram/utils/match-signal.js"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"code889","model":"gpt-5.4-mini","usage":{"input":2621,"output":12492,"cacheRead":78848,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":93961,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774101114575}}
