{"type":"message","id":"c6ddcc87","parentId":"897e8f28","timestamp":"2026-03-21T13:53:45.813Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Exploring event methods**\n\nI’m considering how to streamline events by potentially importing methods like createHeartbeatEvent and others. I noticed the signalClient has existing methods returning booleans, so I think about patching those to return an envelope instead. It could simplify things. But that might break current sending functions.  \nI'll examine game.wxml and game.js where sendQuick methods exist but aren’t tied to the UI. Should I modify match-signal send methods to return envelope objects? It's a bit complicated with existing code expectations, but I’ll think through it!\n\n**Patching match-signal methods**\n\nI'm thinking about patching the match-signal methods to create an envelope, send it, and then return the envelope object. I might need to verify if a `sendEnvelope` method already exists so I can adjust it accordingly. It seems I should also consider adding methods like connectSignal. To do this effectively, I’ll need to look at the current game.wxml content, possibly integrating new inputs and buttons for connect/disconnect and quick actions. I think I’m on the right track here!\n\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_VYydmfsoQIL0oWCG3jIGuz4b","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/gem/workspace/agent/workspace/chinese-chess-minigame/miniprogram/pages/game/game.wxml","limit":260,"offset":1,"path":"/home/gem/workspace/agent/workspace/chinese-chess-minigame/miniprogram/pages/game/game.wxml"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_rjpPi1LrlMDUmximsw05vjDA","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/gem/workspace/agent/workspace/chinese-chess-minigame/miniprogram/pages/game/game.wxss","limit":260,"offset":1,"path":"/home/gem/workspace/agent/workspace/chinese-chess-minigame/miniprogram/pages/game/game.wxss"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_X7b2zR