{"type":"message","id":"31eba1c9","parentId":"cdcf5458","timestamp":"2026-03-21T19:01:46.199Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_1rCPiyUFEm8zwo9SYkRETRCN","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/gem/workspace/agent/workspace/chinese-chess-minigame/miniprogram/utils/chess-engine.js","limit":120,"offset":330,"path":"/home/gem/workspace/agent/workspace/chinese-chess-minigame/miniprogram/utils/chess-engine.js"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"code889","model":"gpt-5.4-mini","usage":{"input":217,"output":78,"cacheRead":68608,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":68903,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774119701387}}
{"type":"message","id":"3272f673","parentId":"31eba1c9","timestamp":"2026-03-21T19:01:46.210Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_1rCPiyUFEm8zwo9SYkRETRCN","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"function advanceGame(board, move) {\n  const next = cloneBoard(board);\n  const piece = next.pieces.find((p) => p.id === move.pieceId && p.alive);\n  const target = getPieceAt(next, move.to.x, move.to.y);\n  if (target) target.alive = false;\n  piece.pos = { x: move.to.x, y: move.to.y };\n  next.lastMove = { pieceId: piece.id, from: { ...move.from }, to: { ...move.to }, capturedPieceId: target ? target.id : null };\n  next.moveHistory = [...next.moveHistory, next.lastMove];\n  next.currentSide = oppositeSide(board.currentSide);\n  next.selectedPieceId = null;\n\n  const sideToMove = next.currentSide;\n  const legalMoves = getLegalMoves(next, sideToMove);\n  if (legalMoves.length === 0) {\n    if (isInCheck(next, sideToMove)) {\n      next.status = 'checkmate';\n      next.winner = oppositeSide(sideToMove);\n    } else {\n      next.status = 'draw';\n      next.winner = null;\n    }\n  } else if (isInCheck(next, sideToMove)) {\n    next.status = 'check';\n    next.winner = null;\n  } else {\n    next.status = 'playing';\n    next.winner = null;\n  }\n  return next;\n}\n\nconst PIECE_LABELS = {\n  red: {\n    rook: '车', horse: '马', elephant: '相', advisor: '仕', general: '帅', cannon: '炮', soldier: '兵',\n  },\n  black: {\n    rook: '车', horse: '马', elephant: '象', advisor: '士', general: '将', cannon: '炮', soldier: '卒',\n  },\n};\n\nfunction pieceLabel(piece) {\n  return PIECE_LABELS[piece.side][piece.type] || '?';\n}\n\nfunction searchBestMove(board, { side = board.currentSide, depth = 1, timeLimitMs = 60 } = {}) {\n  const legal = getLegalMoves(board, side);\n  if (!legal.length) return null;\n\n  let bestMove = legal[0];\n  let bestScore = -Infinity;\n  for (const move of legal) {\n    const next = advanceGame(board, move);\n    let score = 0;\n    if (move.capturedPieceId) score += 1000;\n    if (next.status === 'checkmate') score += 99999;\n    if (next.status === 'check') score += 30;\n    if (move.pieceId.includes('r') && move.to.y < move.from.y) score += 1;\n    if (score > bestScore) {\n      bestScore = score;\n      bestMove = move;\n    }\n  }\n  return bestMove;\n}\n\nfunction replayMoves(initialBoard, moves) {\n  return moves.reduce((board, move) => advanceGame(board, move), initialBoard);\n}\n\nmodule.exports = {\n  BOARD_WIDTH,\n  BOARD_HEIGHT,\n  Side,\n  PieceType,\n  oppositeSide,\n  isInsideBoard,\n  createInitialBoard,\n  cloneBoard,\n  getPieceAt,\n  getLegalMoves,\n  isInCheck,\n  advanceGame,\n  searchBestMove,\n  pieceLabel,\n  replayMoves,\n};\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774119706203}}
{"type":"message","id":"62bc338d","parentId":"3272f673","timestamp":"2026-03-21T19:02:08.119Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Considering game state management**\n\nI think we should implement envelope handling in game.js to check envelope.type for actions like move, sync, draw, and resign, which would update the game board and local state. Since the game engine board is the authoritative source, in online mode, incoming moves should advance the game and update or sync the board. It's necessary to create functions in game.js for handling these envelopes and outgoing actions. Using a transport config path in app.json might not be the best idea, though.\n\n**Modifying game logic**\n\nI need to modify the WXML with a signal URL input and buttons, while also updating game.js. In onLoad, I want to create a client with handlers for applySignalEnvelope, possibly adding a method called handleSignalEnvelope. When connecting to the signal, using a fallback signal URL or auto-connect from a stored URL might work well. I should ensure names are consistent, like simulateOnlineRequest. I'll need to make significant edits to game.js, adding new methods and renaming some wrappers for clarity. Let's justify the desired implementation.\n\n**Synchronizing game board**\n\nI could sync the current board based on the room, but I need to ensure that remote accept doesn’t alter the board. For moves, if the move payload exists, I should apply that move to the current board only if it's valid and coming from a remote source. If a remote move arrives and the board matches, I'll advance the game if the move is legal; otherwise, I can log it and ignore it. For synchronization, I should replace the board with a valid payload.board, checking its shape with cloneBoard, and updating markers based on the last move.\n\n**Updating board and methods**\n\nI could reconstruct board.currentSide as needed, and for different actions like ack, heartbeat, draw.offer, draw.response, resign, or error, I should update the room and set logs accordingly. \n\nFor outgoing send methods, I might want to send from the local board and room state. It would be good to expose connectSignal for using the input URL. When a match button is clicked, I could use signalClient.sendMatchRequest. While the WXML buttons are for simulateOnlineRequest, I can consider repurposing them for actual protocol messages if connected. But I need to keep user preferences in mind for a true WebSocket signal layer.\n\n**Considering AI suppression**\n\nIf the online connection uses the same page, I’m thinking it might be necessary to suppress the AI when online. There's a `state.mode` in `createGameState`, so I should investigate if it involves the AI or local functions. I really want to make sure I check the `createGameState` details to understand how this works better. It feels important to get that right for functionality!\n\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_AS1WCisLzlLEGFW9ywNBSRxN","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/gem/workspace/agent/workspace/chinese-chess-minigame/miniprogram/utils/game-state.js","limit":200,"offset":1,"path":"/home/gem/workspace/agent/workspace/chinese-chess-minigame/miniprogram/utils/game-state.js"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"code889","model":"gpt-5.4-mini","usage":{"input":1007,"output":2636,"cacheRead":68608,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":72251,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774119706209}}
